[
  "div",
  {
    "className": "content-wrapper"
  },
  [
    "h1",
    {},
    "Relative Pronouns I: Que"
  ],
  [
    "p",
    {},
    [
      "Relative pronouns are used to connect two sentences that share a common noun. ",
      [
        "strong",
        {},
        "Que"
      ],
      " is the most common relative pronoun in Spanish."
    ]
  ],
  [
    "h2",
    {},
    "Using 'Que'"
  ],
  [
    "p",
    {},
    [
      "Unlike in English, where you can often omit 'that' (the book [that] I read), in Spanish you ",
      [
        "strong",
        {},
        "must"
      ],
      " always use 'que'."
    ]
  ],
  [
    "ul",
    {
      "className": "phrase-list"
    },
    [
      "li",
      {},
      "'Que' can refer to people or things."
    ],
    [
      "li",
      {},
      "It translates to: that, which, who, whom."
    ]
  ],
  [
    "h2",
    {},
    "Examples"
  ],
  [
    "ul",
    {
      "className": "phrase-list"
    },
    [
      "li",
      {},
      [
        "span",
        {
          "className": "spanish"
        },
        [
          "El libro ",
          [
            "strong",
            {},
            "que"
          ],
          " compré es bueno."
        ]
      ],
      [
        "span",
        {
          "className": "meaning"
        },
        "The book (that) I bought is good."
      ]
    ],
    [
      "li",
      {},
      [
        "span",
        {
          "className": "spanish"
        },
        [
          "La mujer ",
          [
            "strong",
            {},
            "que"
          ],
          " habla es mi tía."
        ]
      ],
      [
        "span",
        {
          "className": "meaning"
        },
        "The woman who is speaking is my aunt."
      ]
    ]
  ]
]